President Obama has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the Holy See to attend a ceremony where two American Archbishops will be elevated to Cardinals. The delegation will be led by U.S. Ambassador to the Holy See, Miguel H. Díaz, and includes Kenneth F. Hackett, President Emeritus of Catholic Relief Services. The ceremony will take place on February 18 and will see Archbishop Timothy M. Dolan of New York and Archbishop Edwin F. O’Brien of Baltimore elevated to the College of Cardinals.